tspan.tspan: I'm sure you've been pulled from your lean before
in bloodless warfare by the unreclined.
They flood you, leaner, mired in torture,
bending your frame to fit picture refined
to please their perspective, favouring lines
frantic and sharply angled to viewer -
slicing resting subject with tax and fines
on taking time to admire leisure.
Entitiled owners see terrorism
viewing undemanding hedonism.
"I see wisdom in thumb-sucking baby
but weep too, from knowing a quietude
is found so young by self-sufficiency,
unguarded from insular attitude
and worse the ones that paint themselves abloom -
representation that's not a flower,
flaunting petals still, giving no perfume.
We trusted their promise of an offer
but learned to live life aloof on treason.
I offer my thumb for its our season.
"You take in all labels like scattered seeds,
not one to bite off pacifying thumb -
even those off-green. Parasitic weeds
numb their brain stem for undeserved aplomb.
They tend you so only they propagate
feeding suicide candy to unchecked
demeanours - should they spore, greener worlds wait,
heeding multiplied hands meeting reject,
growing fungi-algae to great effect,
I've only found help from class imperfect."
The leaner laid cradled, captured by thought.
He felt eons pass, felt vestigial,
before now, before he found that unsought
external hand reach out - so trivial,
but then, why so individual too?
He'd lived like others, roots entrenched in ground,
limbs stretched for solitude, alone they grew,
breathing CO2 as clouds danced around.
Rivers dried, animals died, unnoticed.
Now stray branch bridged untapped brain unfocused.
